🧠 2. Spoken vs Written (this is HUGE)

This is where most people miss the real difference.

⸻

🟣 Sanskrit

Spoken
	•	Ultra-precise phonetics
	•	Sound = meaning carrier
	•	Pronunciation errors matter

Written
	•	Secondary to sound
	•	Script changed over time (Devanagari, etc.)

👉 Core idea:

Sanskrit = sound-first system


⸻

🔵 Arabic

Spoken
	•	Many dialects (can differ a lot)
	•	Everyday speech diverges

Written (especially Qur’anic Arabic)
	•	Extremely fixed
	•	Standardized grammar + form

👉 Core idea:

Arabic = written sacred anchor + spoken variation


⸻

🟡 Hebrew

Spoken
	•	Revived modern Hebrew ≠ ancient exactly
	•	Evolved naturally

Written
	•	Ancient texts preserved
	•	Originally consonant-heavy (no vowels)

👉 Core idea:

Hebrew = structural skeleton (roots) + evolving expression


